===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|木|丮|t1=sapling|t2=kneeling person; to hold|ls=ic}} – a kneeling person planting a sapling, hence “to plant”. The original character of {{zh-l|*蓺}} and {{zh-l|*藝}}.

Sometimes {{zh-l|*土|soil}} was added underneath the sapling; the two then merged into unrelated {{zh-l|*坴}}, with the top component {{zh-l|*圥}} resulting from corruption of {{zh-l|*木}}. The {{zh-l|*丮}} component on the right side of the character evolved into {{zh-l|*丸}}. 

This character {{och-l|埶}} was also often phonetically borrowed to represent {{och-l|勢|influence; power}}.

